Legal & General Group Plc: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 25, 2017 12:36 PM ET
Insurance

Company Overview of Legal & General Group Plc



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Legal & General Group Plc provides various insurance products and services worldwide. It operates through Legal & General Retirement (LGR), Legal & General Investment Management (LGIM), Legal & General Capital (LGC), Legal & General Insurance (LGI), Savings, and General Insurance (GI) segments. The LGR segment provides annuity contracts with guaranteed income for a specified time; longevity insurance products for company pension schemes; and lifetime mortgages. The LGIM segment offers index fund management; active fixed income and liquidity management; solution and liability driven investment; active equity; and real estate funds. The LGC segment provides direct investments with a focus on h...
Legal & General Group Plc provides various insurance products and services worldwide. It operates through Legal & General Retirement (LGR), Legal & General Investment Management (LGIM), Legal & General Capital (LGC), Legal & General Insurance (LGI), Savings, and General Insurance (GI) segments. The LGR segment provides annuity contracts with guaranteed income for a specified time; longevity insurance products for company pension schemes; and lifetime mortgages. The LGIM segment offers index fund management; active fixed income and liquidity management; solution and liability driven investment; active equity; and real estate funds. The LGC segment provides direct investments with a focus on housing, infrastructure, and SME financing, as well as provides investments on treasury and traded assets. The LGI segment offers retail and group protection products; individual term assurance, which provides death benefits; universal life contracts, including savings and death benefits; and unit and index linked savings products, bank based investment accounts, and corporate pension products. The Savings segment provides individual and corporate pensions; endowment policies; with-profits bonds; and participating contracts. The GI segment offers household and accident, sickness, unemployment, and pet insurance products. The company is also involved in treasury, institutional fund, real estate agency, and reinsurance activities. In addition, it provides property, equity, mixed asset, fixed interest, and debt security unit trust products, as well as develops building projects and modular housings. Legal & General Group Plc was founded in 1836 and is based in London, the United Kingdom.
Detailed Description


