Legal & General Group Plc Key Developments

Legal and General Group Names Emma Byron to the Managing Director of Individual Annuities
Jul 5 17
Legal and General Group named Emma Byron to the post of managing director of individual annuities. Byron will be part of the retail retirement division. She previously headed the group financial planning and analysis function at the insurer's retirement unit.


Legal & General Group Plc - Shareholder/Analyst Call
Jun 13 17
Legal & General Group Plc - Shareholder/Analyst Call


JV Partners Of Indiafirst Life Insurance Reported Exploring Strategic Options
Jun 12 17
JV partners of IndiaFirst Life Insurance Company Limited reportedly are exploring strategic options. ET NOW learns that a mega deal is brewing in IndiaFirst Life Insurance, which is a three-way joint venture between Bank of Baroda (BSE:532134), Legal & General Group Plc (LSE:LGEN) and Andhra Bank (BSE:532418). According to two sources familiar with the proposed transaction who spoke on the condition of anonymity, the JV partners are currently exploring multiple strategic options which could include either a potential partial stake sale or even a potential exit based on the progress of the discussions. "JV partners are considering various strategic options, but no plans have been finalised as yet by them. As part of preliminary negotiations, talks have been held with prospective suitors like Reliance Nippon Life Insurance Company Limited," said one of the two sources. "AMBIT Capital Private Limited has been roped in to advice on the strategic options suitable for each of the JV partners. For instance, Legal & General Group is reconsidering its emerging markets strategy and is believed to be eyeing an exit," added the second source cited above. Ambit Capital declined to comment on market speculation while IndiaFirst Life Insurance said, "IndiaFirst Life Insurance has had no discussions with any insurance company, nor has appointed any advisor for any such arrangement."


